@Service
public class OrderService {

    @Autowired
    private KafkaTemplate<String, Order> kafkaTemplate;

    public void createOrder(Order order) {
        // Begin a transaction
        kafkaTemplate.executeInTransaction((txKafkaTemplate) -> {
            try {
                // Publish event to Kafka
                txKafkaTemplate.send("order_created", order);

                // Commit the transaction if successful
                return true;
            } catch (Exception e) {
                System.err.println("Failed to send order creation event: " + e.getMessage());
                // Abort the transaction on failure
                return false;
            }
        });
    }

    public void updateOrder(Order order) {
        kafkaTemplate.executeInTransaction((txKafkaTemplate) -> {
            try {
                txKafkaTemplate.send("order_updated", order);
                return true;
            } catch (Exception e) {
                System.err.println("Failed to send order update event: " + e.getMessage());
                return false;
            }
        });
    }
}
```

### 4. **Transaction Management in Consumers**
Ensure that your consumers manage transactions correctly to ensure exactly-once semantics.

#### Example Service:
